These queries retrieve the menu items from the respective categories.

1. SELECT VegStarters, VegSoups, VegMainCourse FROM foodmenu (and similarly for Non-Veg categories)

These queries retrieve all the menu items from the respective categories.

To create the tables and insert sample data, you can use the following SQL queries:


CREATE TABLE foodmenu (
  VegStarters VARCHAR(100),
  VegSoups VARCHAR(100),
  VegMainCourse VARCHAR(100),
  NonVegStarters VARCHAR(100),
  NonVegSoups VARCHAR(100),
  NonvegMainCourse VARCHAR(100)
);

INSERT INTO foodmenu (VegStarters, VegSoups, VegMainCourse, NonVegStarters, NonVegSoups, NonvegMainCourse)
VALUES 
('Veg Starter 1', 'Veg Soup 1', 'Veg Main Course 1', 'Non-Veg Starter 1', 'Non-Veg Soup 1', 'Non-Veg Main Course 1'),
('Veg Starter 2', 'Veg Soup 2', 'Veg Main Course 2', 'Non-Veg Starter 2', 'Non-Veg Soup 2', 'Non-Veg Main Course 2'),
('Veg Starter 3', 'Veg Soup 3', 'Veg Main Course 3', 'Non-Veg Starter 3', 'Non-Veg Soup 3', 'Non-Veg Main Course 3');

